GM2Calc
=======

GM2Calc calculates the SUSY contributions to a_mu = (g-2)/2 in the
real MSSM.

Homepage:                https://gm2calc.hepforge.org
Source code repository:  https://github.com/gm2calc
                         https://github.com/FlexibleSUSY
References:              arxiv:XXXX.YYYY


Requirements
============

 * C++ compiler (g++ >= 4.4.7 or clang++ >= 3.1 or icpc >= 12.1)
 * Fortran compiler (gfortran, ifort)
 * Boost (version 1.37.0 or higher)   http://www.boost.org
 * Eigen 3 (version 3.1 or higher)    http://eigen.tuxfamily.org
 * Lapack / Blas                      http://www.netlib.org/lapack/


Compilation
===========

To compile the GM2Calc run

  $ make

The used compilers, include paths and libraries can be passed as an
argument to make.  For example:

  $ make \
       CXX=icpc \
       FC=ifort \
       FLIBS="-L/opt/intel/2015/lib/intel64 -lifcore -limf -lintlc" \
       EIGENFLAGS="-I/opt/eigen3/eigen3" \
       BOOSTFLAGS="-I/opt/boost/include"

In the following list all supported variables and their default values
are given:

  CXX             := g++
  CPPFLAGS        := -I. -Isrc
  CXXFLAGS        := -O2 -std=c++11
  CXX_DEP_GEN     := g++
  FC              := gfortran
  FFLAGS          := -O2 -frecursive
  FLIBS           := -lgfortran -lm
  FOR_DEP_GEN     := gfortran
  MAKELIB         := ar cru
  BLASLIBS        := -lblas
  BOOSTFLAGS      := -I/usr/include
  EIGENFLAGS      := -I/usr/include/eigen3
  LAPACKLIBS      := -llapack -lblas


Running GM2Calc
===============

GM2Calc can be run with (i) either an SLHA interface or with (ii) a
custom GM2Calc interface (similar to SLHA, but different definition of
input parameters).  See `bin/gm2.x --help' for all options.

Example using the SLHA interface:

  $ bin/gm2.x --slha-input-file=input/slha.in

or

  $ cat input/slha.in | bin/gm2.x --slha-input-file=-

Example using the GM2Calc interface:

  $ bin/gm2.x --gm2calc-input-file=input/gm2calc.in

or

  $ cat input/gm2calc.in | bin/gm2.x --gm2calc-input-file=-
